main event: A civilian observed a star-like object displaying unusual movements and colors in the sky in Lexington, Kentucky on October 3, 1966.
interesting points: The observer noted that the object twinkled and changed colors, moving rapidly and briefly disappearing from view., The sighting lasted for about 60 minutes with continuous observations for five to ten minutes., The object exhibited slow circling motions and a pulsing effect similar to neon lights., The observer initially mistook the object for a star before realizing it was moving., The report includes a letter from Project Blue Book requesting further information on the sighting.
witness description: A civilian named M.D. who was returning home from a scout meeting.
